Response 1:
I am part of this study looking at the spread of the immune response in SARS-CoV-2 infected hamsters with my old group in New York and we are close to publication (manuscript accepted in Science Signaling with minor revisions).
I was involved at an earlier time in this project but when I left another postdoc took the lead. As part of the review (and official acceptance process) we need an official letter from an independent person to attest to the proper use of statistical methods and that the results can be verified. In this work we didn’t do any modeling nor any statistical inference, just regular bulk RNA-seq and some standard tests for significance (t-tests, ANOVAs, etc. using mainly prism).
I was wondering if anyone at DaSL know who would be available/willing to review the analyses and attest on their validity (or suggest other type of analyses in its defect). We will of course acknowledge all help in the manuscript.
